      "section": [
        "Fire Nation train engineer",
        "History"
      ],
      "text": "One day, the train on which this engineer was working was visited by Avatar Aang, who was undercover at the time, and his friend, Sokka. The two also brought along a little girl named Sho, who would be riding the train to get to her grandmother's house."
    },
    {
      "body": "Unbeknownst to them, they were being followed by a ${link_0} assassin nicknamed \"Combustion Man\". With his overdeveloped third eye, he shot a beam of light at the Avatar, causing part of the train to explode. Consequently, the engineer hit his head and passed out, leaving the train without a controller. The ${link_1} attempted to contact him, but to no avail. Sokka set out to the engine's cab, where the unconscious engineer was located, to slow the train down.",
      "links": [
        {
          "body": "firebending",
          "key": "${link_0}",
          "target": {
            "external": false,
            "href": "/wiki/Firebending",
            "page": "Firebending"
          }
        },
        {
          "body": "conductor",
          "key": "${link_1}",
          "target": {
            "external": false,
            "href": "/wiki/Fire_Nation_train_conductor",
            "page": "Fire_Nation_train_conductor"
